cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.NI 

The paper discusses a connectionist approach to data mining using neural networks for classification rule extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves machine learning and data mining, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The use of neural networks for classification also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experimental results and comparison with previously published works, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
